  "overview": {
    "value": "Gravity-1 is a solid-propellant, expendable, medium-lift launch vehicle designed, manufactured and launched by Orienspace, capable of carrying up to 6.5 t to low Earth orbit or 4.2 t to a 500 km sun-synchronous orbit. It consists of seven solid rocket motors and launches from a sea platform; its maiden flight, from a converted barge off Haiyang on 11 January 2024, set a record as the world's most powerful solid-fuel carrier rocket. The reported launch cost is around US$39 million.",
